The unimaginable has happened. The country has, for all intents and purposes, been shut down because it is under attack. It was surreal watching President Cyril Ramaphosa in military fatigues addressing the SA National Defence Force, exhorting them to go out and “defend our people against this invisible enemy”. It must have been quite irresistibly tempting for his political opponents to have a go at him for “wearing a uniform he didn’t earn”, so much so that the minister of defence had to come out and defend him the following day. The president’s critics missed the big point he was...